Seeking resignation of Union Ministers Smriti Irani and Bandaru Dattatreya accusing them of having role in the suicide of Rohit Vemula, a research scholar at the Central University of Hyderabad, a group of Youth Congress activists took out a march to the Central University of Keralaâ€™s Periye campus here on Monday.The march, as part of the nationwide agitation by the Youth Congress Parliamentary Committee, was inaugurated by former State Youth Congress President T. Siddique.Addressing the function, Mr. Siddique alleged that the Narendra Modi government was turning Central universities in the country as centres of intolerance by depriving freedom and perpetuating inequality on campuses.